tags.description: Farthest left route on Bob's wall. Climb up face to hand/fist crack.
tags.name: There is somethng About Bob

tags.description: Hard moves up face to thin horizontal, move right slightly then fire for the top. Nice.
tags.name: Bob's Your Uncle

tags.description: Face climb past 2 bolts to ledge then 2 more bolts to anchor. Careful getting to 3rd bolt but it's very easy.
tags.name: Bob The Builder

tags.description: Start in a left facing corner. Once that ends [crux] diagonal right up the face.
tags.name: This Bob's For You

tags.description: Start on a slab [small TCU off right] to a right rising ramp. Finish above the ramps end.
tags.name: The Bobbit

tags.description: Start low at base of sloping rock, climb past 1 bolt to ledge then up clean face.
tags.name: AMP

tags.description: This is the route that named the wall. A thin vertical crack with a horizontal crack 2/3 way up. The crux is passing the cross but finishing is no easy feat either. Many hard moves very few rests. The bottom is a little funky to protect but the crux is so
tags.name: What About Bob? aka Croix de pierre

tags.description: This is the left facing corner just left of Shish Kebob. Stays wet after rain.
tags.name: Sponge Bob

tags.description: Start left of Shish Kebob, between face and tree. Make a hardish face move to the first bolt and continue along the green face to the second bolt. Finish a nice clean face with 2 more bolts. A spicy route.
tags.name: Plumb Bob

tags.description: The farthest route right. Starts a few meters left of the pine tree and follow a right arching line of tightly spaced bolts. The last moves are the crux but the very top is a bucket. This route was really spicy before the broken pine limbs were trimmed.
tags.name: Shish Kebob

tags.description: Start near the mouth of the cave on right. Traverse out right to an overhang and easier crack finish.
tags.name: Slippery in Duckies

tags.description: Climb steep jugs to technical face to arete.
tags.name: Closed Project

tags.description: Climb the left arete on the buttress.
tags.name: Peter's unnamed route

tags.description: Face climb past 2 bolts right of a buttress.
tags.name: Icicle

tags.description: Climb the pillar left of the Elephant Cave to under a large chockstone.
tags.name: Frozen Mammoth

tags.description: The climb is on the upper level, above and downhill from the main cliff face. Can be accessed by either climbing a route and going up and following a trail left or ... walking up the main face to "the gully" then following one of many trails on the left g
tags.name: Out of Tolerance

tags.description: Another short bolted route, crux is at the top.
tags.name: UnNamed_1

tags.description: Short medium tough bolted route.
tags.name: UnNamed_2

tags.description: Working on this.
tags.name: Closed project anchor

tags.description: left of the left bolt line.
tags.name: My First Time Left

tags.description: left of the dihedral right of the left bolt line.
tags.name: My First Time Right

tags.description: Goes up the huge dihedral.
tags.name: Why Nuts

tags.description: This route goes in the open book and through the triangle roof to a surprise hold.
tags.name: Up Close and Personal

tags.description: Short route but worth it ! climbs a small crack to the left with a right pull!
tags.name: Stocking With No Legs

tags.description: Starts on the ledge, climb the steep red face with a tiny crack in the middle. This route as been tried by many but still awaits its first free ascents.
tags.name: In the Red

tags.description: This route starts on the ledge and goes a little right once you past the first 2 bolts its a nice face to the anchors . there is a hidden hold for the second bolt!
tags.name: Middle Age Crisis

tags.description: Climb the arete beside the pinnacle.
tags.name: Killer Bunnies from Mars / Attack of the Killer Bunnies

tags.description: Start in the middle of a blank wall to the right of a very high bolt. Make hard face move up a thin face to a high first bolt. Make the crux move to the second bolt, then climb left to a spot under roof/corner. Turn corner to the right and finish on posit
tags.name: Next Step

tags.description: Climb face to a small roof [crux] followed by a left facing corner.
tags.name: Premier pas

tags.description: Overhanging start on positive holds.
tags.name: Morning After

tags.description: Face climb up low angle face. A little heady.
tags.name: Pine Sol

tags.description: This is the beautiful face. Slightly overhanging at it's top with good holds. Climb up to stance above first bolt, then finesse your way right through the right leaning ramp/corner. Back left to a good stance above second bolt. Straight up the clean rock
tags.name: 40 foot Smurf

tags.description: Very popular route, beginning is deceptive and often gives climbers trouble. Try to keep the barn door closed as you make your way up the corner to reach the crux exit. Finish on easy jugs moves and widely spaced bolts.  A key block fell out at the top of
tags.name: Sidewinder

tags.description: Start atop the Anal Intruder, grab a couple of jagged hold. Now fire up the overhang past 2 bolts and slap for a jug on the arete [crux]. Finish easily in the right facing dihedral. If top roping this one beware of the rope stretch and the large boulder a
tags.name: Sputnik [aka Nickie's Dickie]

tags.description: Climb the obvious large right facing dihedral.
tags.name: The Dihedral

tags.description: Follow line of bolts to a fun finish.
tags.name: Brûle pour ciel

tags.description: A little right of "Brûle pour Ciel" is an obvious blocky easy-looking corner. Climb this on big holds and big ledges.
tags.name: Blocky Corner

tags.description: Climb up on positive holds to a bolt on a diamond shaped slab. Move up onto the left side of the slab, then step right into a v-slot to find Gunks style holds. Finish easier past 2 more bolt to a nice ledge at the top.
tags.name: Kegel Krunch

tags.description: Left route of the 5.10 trio that share an anchor. Look for a slabby triangle of rock, Climb straight up, clip a bolt and make a tricky move into the left facing corner.
tags.name: The Corner

tags.description: Center of trio.  Climb up and make delicate moves past 2 bolts. Now find the G-Spot and make a long powerful move to a side crimp.
tags.name: G-Spot

tags.description: Climb up steep large holds aiming for a flake. Get your feet up and make a reachy move to a good crimp high and right.
tags.name: VD

tags.description: Nice moves down low and kind of ledgy up high.  This route was TR'ed for decades before Bonnie came along and called it 'Bolt Me'. So we did. Now called Stigmata because of an injury to the palm of my hand.
tags.name: Stigmata

tags.description: Obvious crack left of the obvious offwidth about 30m left of gully.
tags.name: The Crack

tags.description: The obvious offwidth 30m left of gully.
tags.name: The Offwidth

tags.description: The large leaning dihedral with a tree at it's base that punishes any top-roper that fails.
tags.name: Booty and the Hoe Fish

tags.description: The "arête" on the rock face just to the left of Bunny Hop.
tags.name: Bunny Arete

tags.description: Nice warm-up route, easy to access, good spot too practice technique, an easy but heady climb.
tags.name: Bunny Hop

tags.description: Start left and climb right, making a long reach through the bulge. One very hard move! Now get your lard ass up there if you can. Much harder for short climbers.
tags.name: Manny the Woolly Mammoth

tags.description: Face climb past closely spaced bots. Often wet.
tags.name: Sid the Sloth

tags.description: Face climb past closely spaced bots. Often wet.
tags.name: No More Mr Nice Guy

tags.description: A nice crack high up with a small tree inside it.
tags.name: Tree Crack

tags.description: Make some steep moves with large holds and tricky feet to a ledge near a large block. Finish left using a finger crack to anchor.
tags.name: Former Rock Star

tags.description: Climb out on steep but positive holds to left side of block. Mount block gingerly and finish straight up.
tags.name: Impatience

tags.description: Just right of Impatience and finishes at the same anchor.
tags.name: Actual Porn Star

tags.description: A short section of red rock with a cracked face. Pre-clip the first bolt then fire the line from beneath. A lot steeper than it looks.  Named after a popular British sitcom.
tags.name: Red Dwarf

tags.description: Start the crux thin overhanging crack then climb left. Very hard opening moves. Bring a stick clip !!!
tags.name: Third Generation

tags.description: Delicate face climbing and a BIG move to a BIG jug gets you to the arete exit. The lower clips are easy once you find the correct body position.
tags.name: Samson

tags.description: Start as for Samson but go right immediately. First moves the are toughest, lots of balance needed.
tags.name: Goliath

tags.description: Start right of Rebar ladder.
tags.name: Tremble Cleft

tags.description: First route on left on the wall between the 2 ledges. Starts on the arete and move right.
tags.name: Pourquoi sacrer

tags.description: Start right of Pourquoi sacrer making your way up a dirty corner/face. Aim for a nice clean open book high and slightly right.
tags.name: Over the Edge

tags.description: An old trad route that finishes in a high corner. I think it starts as for Vol de nuit and then traverses the ledge left past Over the Edge and up the dirty corner.
tags.name: Old Route in corner

tags.description: Start on a right rising ramp then climb the left side of the overhanging wall. There is a hidden hold high & left of the 4th bolt but save some juice for the exciting finish.
tags.name: Vol de nuit

tags.description: Start left of Smeg Head then finnish up steep face.
tags.name: La Corneille

tags.description: Left of a high ledge you'll find a route that finishes in a small chimney. Pretty straight forward, although the chimney is hard if you don't see the hidden flake.
tags.name: Smeg Head

tags.description: Start as for Smeg Head then head slightly right.
tags.name: Smeg Variation

tags.description: Steepest climb at Rigaud. Start left of first bolt, climb up and right util you can clip 2nd bolt. Then fire for the top. 5.13a direct start.
tags.name: Discharge

tags.description: Up big holds in a left facing corner to a powerful finish.
tags.name: Pecker Tracks

tags.description: Pucker up and climb the rounded seam.
tags.name: Weeping Butt Crack

tags.description: This climbs the arete.
tags.name: Ottawa Route

tags.description: Between the Ottawa Route and TR Wall is a shallow open book/corner, which is very hard to protect.
tags.name: Hang-On Harvey

tags.description: Easy low angle face with lots of features. A few different variation to try. Great spot for young kids.
tags.name: TR Wall

tags.description: The corner on the left side of Bonnie's wall, not really hard or tricky just awkward. Squeeze whatever part of your body or just lean into Bonnie's wall and push.Almost chimney moves. Another good small practice spot. Get to try stemming/chimney technique
tags.name: Bumcycle

tags.description: Climb the smooth face climb between Bumcycle and Mean Streak. Care is needed to find the small holds.
tags.name: Raspberry

tags.description: Climbs the larger black streak right of Bumcycle.
tags.name: Mean Streak

tags.description: A short route that has no huge challenges, fun for starting climbers. Just choose your holds and climb up the corner.
tags.name: Beginner Delight

tags.description: Thin moves up a slightly overhanging face.
tags.name: Pete's Problem

tags.description: Face climb past 2 bolts to ledge then 2 more bolts to anchor. Careful getting to 3rd bolt but it's very easy.
tags.name: Bob's base
